<TITLE> Korea crush Bangladesh 9-0 in Asia Cup hockey </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh suffered a third consecutive defeat in the Eighth Men's Asia Cup Hockey when they were crushed 9-0 by Korea in a Pool A encounter in Malaysia on Tuesday. Bangladesh conceded four goals in the first half and the game was effectively over. Bangladesh had earlier lost to Japan 5-0 in the first match and suffered a 7-1 thrashing against hosts Malaysia in their second game. bd
